PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1778166669
OL,3,CMan who grabbed woman's hair convicted
OL,4,Cin first sex-based harassment
OL,5,Cprosecution
OL,7,FA train passenger who grabbed a young
OL,8,Fwoman's hair and said "can I kiss you"
OL,9,Fhas been convicted in the first sex-
OL,10,Fbased harassment charge brought by the
OL,11,FBritish Transport Police (BTP) since
OL,12,Fthe law was changed.
OL,14,FDavid Stroud, 44, made sexually
OL,15,Fmotivated comments to the woman on a
OL,16,Ftrain to London on 3 April, two days
OL,17,Fafter a new law came into force
OL,18,Fbanning harassment motivated by a
OL,19,Fperson's sex.
OL,26,@pD@WOUpD@fO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1778166669
OL,3,CMan who grabbed woman's hair convicted
OL,4,Cin first sex-based harassment
OL,5,Cprosecution
OL,7,FHe pleaded guilty to harassing the
OL,8,Fwoman because of her sex at Highbury
OL,9,FCorner Magistrates' Court on Thursday.
OL,11,FProsecutor Paul Okebu told the court
OL,12,FStroud sat next to the woman, who was
OL,13,Fon the phone to her boyfriend at the
OL,14,Ftime, on a train which left Hastings
OL,15,Fat about 8.50pm.
OL,17,FStroud tried to make conversation with
OL,18,Fthe young woman, who attempted to
OL,19,Fignore him as she was a lone female
OL,20,Ftravelling, the prosecutor said.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1778166669
OL,3,CMan who grabbed woman's hair convicted
OL,4,Cin first sex-based harassment
OL,5,Cprosecution
OL,7,FThe court heard Stroud, of Dartford,
OL,8,FKent, was "constantly leaning on to
OL,9,Fthe woman" and got closer, telling her
OL,10,F"you're magical" and grabbing her
OL,11,Fhair, which the victim "perceived to
OL,12,Fbe sexual".
OL,14,FThe woman said she could smell alcohol
OL,15,Fon the defendant's breath.
OL,17,FMr Okebu said the woman said the
OL,18,Fincident "made her feel very
OL,19,Funcomfortable", she felt "cornered"
OL,20,Fand said she told Stroud to get off
OL,21,Fher hair and not touch her.
OL,26,@pD@KOUqD@JO]rD@AOUrD@PO]sD@XOUtD@JO]zD@
OL,26,AJOU{D@NO]{D@ZOU{D@cO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1778166669
OL,3,CMan who grabbed woman's hair convicted
OL,4,Cin first sex-based harassment
OL,5,Cprosecution
OL,7,F"He continued to try to make
OL,8,Fconversation and then asked 'can I
OL,9,Fkiss you?'," Mr Okebu said, to which
OL,10,Fthe woman replied "absolutely not".
OL,12,FStroud, a father-of-two, told the
OL,13,Fwoman "you're never going to find
OL,14,Fsomeone who loves your hair as much as
OL,15,FI do", and she replied "I already have
OL,16,Fsomeone".
OL,18,FThe woman's boyfriend heard the
OL,19,Fcomments over the phone and called
OL,20,FBTP, who arrested Stroud at London
OL,21,FBridge station.
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@LO]rD@SOUrD@bO]uD@GOUwD@EO]wD@
OL,26,AXOUxD@HO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1778166669
OL,3,CMan who grabbed woman's hair convicted
OL,4,Cin first sex-based harassment
OL,5,Cprosecution
OL,7,FWhile under caution Stroud said: "It's
OL,8,Fjust banter, we had banter together,
OL,9,Fdo you know what I mean," the court
OL,10,Fheard.
OL,12,FHe also said: "I've done nothing wrong
OL,13,Fto her."
OL,15,FAlex Chowdhury, defending, told the
OL,16,Fcourt Stroud, a technician at a water
OL,17,Fcompany, had "reflected" on his
OL,18,Foffending.
OL,26,@oD@bOUqD@YO]tD@OOUuD@HO]yD@NOUyD@XO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1778166669
OL,3,CMan who grabbed woman's hair convicted
OL,4,Cin first sex-based harassment
OL,5,Cprosecution
OL,7,F"As a result of reading through the
OL,8,F(court) papers he has realised it's a
OL,9,Flot more than that (banter)," Mr
OL,10,FChowdhury said.
OL,12,FMr Okebu told the bench of
OL,13,Fmagistrates: "Your worships, this is a
OL,14,Fmatter which on another day in
OL,15,Fdifferent circumstances may have
OL,16,Famounted to a sexual assault.
OL,18,F"It is a serious offence, targeting of
OL,19,Fa lone woman on public transport late
OL,20,Fin the evening."
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@]O]uD@NOUzD@AOU|D@PO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1778166669
OL,3,CMan who grabbed woman's hair convicted
OL,4,Cin first sex-based harassment
OL,5,Cprosecution
OL,7,FThe magistrates ordered a pre-sentence
OL,8,Freport and Stroud will be sentenced at
OL,9,Fthe same court on 9 June.
OL,11,FThe new offence, under Section 4B of
OL,12,Fthe Public Order Act 1986, covers
OL,13,Fintentional harassment directed at
OL,14,Fsomeone because of their sex,
OL,15,Fincluding where perpetrators target
OL,16,Fwomen and girls in public places,
OL,17,Fincluding streets, parks and public
OL,18,Ftransport, the Home Office previously
OL,19,Fsaid.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1778166669
OL,3,CMan who grabbed woman's hair convicted
OL,4,Cin first sex-based harassment
OL,5,Cprosecution
OL,7,FBTP previously said the new section
OL,8,F"strengthens existing public order
OL,9,Fpowers by criminalising behaviour
OL,10,Fwhich causes intentional harassment,
OL,11,Falarm or distress because of a
OL,12,Fperson's sex or presumed sex".
OL,14,FWhen the change in the law was
OL,15,Fannounced, safeguarding minister Jess
OL,16,FPhillips said: "If you harass someone
OL,17,Fin public because of their sex, it
OL,18,Fwill not be tolerated and you can face
OL,19,Fa criminal record and up to two years
OL,20,Fbehind bars."
OL,26,@pD@AOUtD@]O]xD@POU|D@MO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1778166669
OL,3,CMan who grabbed woman's hair convicted
OL,4,Cin first sex-based harassment
OL,5,Cprosecution
OL,7,FNathan Miebai, deputy chief Crown
OL,8,Fprosecutor for the West Midlands Crown
OL,9,FProsecution Service, said: "It is
OL,10,Fvital that women and girls feel safe
OL,11,Fin public spaces and able to live
OL,12,Ftheir lives without fear of harassment
OL,13,Fbecause of their sex.
OL,15,F"David Stroud made that impossible for
OL,16,Fone woman who was simply travelling
OL,17,Fhome on the train and today he has
OL,18,Ffaced the consequences of his actions.
OL,26,@qD@\OUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
